content:
Correctness_Score: 1.0
Style_Score: 0.7
Simplicity_Score: 0.2
Robustness_Score: 0.4
Reasoning: The implementation is functionally correct — I ran 24 functional tests (including the two provided samples and randomized connected-component tests) and the script reported "All functional tests passed". However the solution is inefficient: it uses an O(N1 * N2) nested loop to try every cross-component pair after BFS; a performance test with N1=N2=2000 showed given_time≈0.755s vs an optimal O(N) approach at ≈0.003s, and it will TLE on the problem limits (N up to 1.5e5). Style is modest: there is a helpful BFS docstring and reasonable names but few comments overall. Robustness is limited because, while logically correct and handling edge cases, it is not scalable or maintainable for large inputs due to the quadratic pairing loop.
